The paper deals with source and message compression, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT). The use of convex-split and position based decoding techniques suggest that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The consideration of scenarios with and without side information suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM).
